            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>These letters to Henry B. Curtis (b. 1799), a lawyer in Knox County, Ohio, primarily concern legal issues involving claims to land and money. There are also two personal letters to Curtis from his brother, Joseph Eaton, of Scott County, Ill.</p>
                                 <p>Wilbur Duncan of Decatur, Ill., donated these letters to the Survey.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


